# Keep shell scripts LF on every platform. Git for Windows defaults to
# core.autocrlf=true and would otherwise check these out with CRLF, which
# breaks the shebang under Git Bash (bash looks for `bash\r`) and silently
# disables every hook. See v3-007 (Windows deploy) + Claude Code hooks docs:
# on Windows hook commands run under Git Bash, so .sh files MUST be LF.
*.sh text eol=lf

# The plan-gate marker and policy are read by bash; keep them LF too.
*.json text eol=lf
